# Gemini Relay — server environment variables
# Copy to `.env` (or set in Vercel Project → Settings → Environment Variables).
# Never commit real secrets.

# --- Proxy mode (optional for REST; required for MCP) ---
# JSON object of required request headers. All must match (AND).
# Default / example: X-API-KEY. You may add more headers if you want.
# Header names are case-insensitive at runtime (HTTP).
# In .env wrap the JSON in single quotes.
# Server injects a Gemini key from GEMINI_API_KEYS upstream after auth succeeds.

PROXY_AUTH_HEADERS='{"X-API-KEY":"<your-proxy-secret>"}'

# Server Gemini key pool (JSON array). Required for proxy mode.
# One key: '["only-key"]'. Multiple keys + Vercel KV → least-tokens-today rotation.
GEMINI_API_KEYS='["key-a","key-b"]'

# Vercel KV / Upstash REST (optional). Needed for least-tokens-today rotation when ≥2 keys.
# This project’s store typically exposes prefixed vars (copy from Vercel → Env):
# GEMINI_RELAY_KV_REST_API_URL=https://….kv.vercel-storage.com
# GEMINI_RELAY_KV_REST_API_TOKEN=…
# Fallbacks also accepted: KV_REST_API_URL / KV_REST_API_TOKEN, or UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_*.
# Do not use READ_ONLY_TOKEN (needs INCRBY). KV_URL / REDIS_URL are redis:// — ignored here.

# --- Passthrough mode (REST / Playground only; not accepted by MCP) ---
# Callers send their own Gemini key via `?key=` or Header `x-goog-api-key`.
# Playground stores the key in browser localStorage and uses passthrough by default.

# --- MCP ---
# HTTP MCP at `/api/mcp` requires proxy mode (PROXY_AUTH_HEADERS + GEMINI_API_KEYS).
# One tool: gemini_list_models (smoke test). Skill: `/skills/gemini-relay-skill.md`.
